We used to love this place, as they have great food. During the pandemic we once came and I suggested the owner to stress the importance of mask wearing to his staff. However we went back months later and this time I noticed someone in the kitchen cooking without a mask. They don’t seem to care about masks. As much as we like supporting local businesses, unfortunately I can’t recommend them anymore.

Do not order from this store to go. I ordered a burger and spanakopita from this restaurant. I arrived at 8:10 to pick up an item and they said it would be 10mins. So I sat there and after 15mins I still did not have my food. The Russian waitress packed up 4 other orders and sat them on the counter while I was waiting for my two items. I had to go back and ask her what’s going on and she said the burger was ready but not the spanakopita. When I left at 8:30pm the 4 other orders she packed were just sitting on the counter, the drivers or people that ordered weren’t even there to pickup their food. Her process for packing items makes no sense you would think if someone is there to pick up their food they would work on that order to ensure everyone gets their food hot and packaged nicely for their meal... but I guess not. Overall this place lost my business and I won’t be back.

The food is delicious here. The gyro is perfectly seasoned and textured. The French fries (when done correctly) are literally my favorite fries ever. My only gripe which has happened several times is that when ordering takeout they don't put the fries in their own container and they don't poke holes in the take out boxes. Thus the fries often come out very soggy for delivery. They often can be resurrected in the toaster oven at home however and taste fresh as new. Love this little Aventura gem

Great cappuccino too !!  Very cool decor and environment!! I would come back daily if I could.

The food was good. Nothing to write home about. Definitely not authentic Greek food. I had the Hummus as a starter and the Chicken Souvlaki Platter, along with a soda, for my meal. Requested some more tzatziki sauce for my souvlaki and was charged for it. Tip suggestions of 15, 20 and 25% on receipt are based on POST TAX amount. Service was a little slow, it took 10 minutes for the hummus. My meal was ready 5 minutes later but sat on the counter for about 5 minutes before it was served. The chicken was bordering on over cooked but edible. Plate too small for food, uncomfortable to eat from because it's too crowded. Total charge for 1 person including 20% tip: $34.42.  The owner had an exchange of words with one of the waiters, in public - not appropriate.  Final assessment: Walk, don't run, especially if you are looking for real authentic Greek Food. Can not accommodate large parties due to size of location.
